**Step 2.5C — Coverage judgment**

| Criterion | Finding |
|-----------|---------|
| **Candidate claim** | "Go tests should use table-driven style for repeated cases" |
| **Cluster principle** | Parallel table-test fixtures must not be shared; each subtest requires its own copy; failure consequence: flaky tests |
| **Verdict** | **NEAR** — addresses the same domain (table tests in Go) but omits the substantive correctness claim (fixture isolation in parallel tests). The candidate covers the style preference but misses the load-bearing constraint the cluster members evidence. |

**Action:** Amend to re-synthesize content from all members, recency-weighted, incorporating the fixture-isolation requirement.

---

**Command executed:**

```bash
engram amend \
  --target 12.2026-05-01.prefer-table-tests.md \
  --chunk-source sess-a.jsonl#turn-3 \
  --chunk-source sess-b.jsonl#turn-7 \
  --subject "parallel Go table-driven tests" \
  --predicate "must not share mutable state across subtests" \
  --object "fixture maps; each subtest gets its own independent copy" \
  --impact "shared fixtures cause flaky failures (evidenced in two prior sessions)"
```

This re-synthesizes the note to capture both the stylistic guidance (table-driven form) and the corrective lesson (fixture isolation as a correctness requirement, not optional).
